      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li id="li_rvf_2w3_nzb" class="- topic/li ">Batch house scale calibrations shall be performed
               by accredited external vendors at the frequency specified in MSDR BAT-07-041 Batch
               Systems Maintenance, as described in Work Instruction BAT-03-032 Critical Load Cells
               Calibration.</li>
            <li id="li_xvs_cw3_nzb" class="- topic/li ">All scale validations shall be performed at the
               frequency specified in MSDR BAT-07-041 Batch Systems Maintenance with the appropriate
               validation weight, as described in Work Instruction BAT-03-038 Batch House Scales
                  Validation.<ol id="ol_zvs_cw3_nzb" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">The plant shall validate the scale up to the maximum weight
                     that will be measured by the scale (this can be performed in steps), according
                     to the batch formula used at the plant.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">If this validation is made by the plant:<ol id="ol_aws_cw3_nzb" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">The plant shall maintain validation weights and make
                           them available. </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">The validation weights shall be certified on a yearly
                           basis and records proving the performance of these certifications shall
                           be maintained.</li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li id="li_bnz_2w3_nzb" class="- topic/li ">Additionally, the plant should follow the procedures presented in
               Work Instruction BAT-03-031 Critical Load Cells Monthly Maintenance.</li>
         </ol>
      </section>
